'''Sumikomorida Kofun''' (墨小盛田古墳, also pronounced as Sumiko Morita Kofun<ref name=Shisui>{{Cite web|和書|author=Shisui Town Hall|url=https://www.town.shisui.chiba.jp/navi/mobile/id/374.html|title=Sumikomorida Kofun|work=Shisui Tourism Navi|accessdate=2020-08-20}}</ref>) is a {{ill|Square Kofun|ja|方墳|1=Square Kofun|1=Square Kofun}} located in {{ill|Shisui, Chiba|ja|酒々井町}}, {{ill|Chiba Prefecture|ja|千葉県}}, Japan.

== Overview ==
The Kofun measures approximately 30 meters north-south, 23 meters east-west, and 3 meters in height. Rectangular Kofuns are a characteristic type of kofun found in the {{ill|Shimousa Province|ja|下総国}} region during the late {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代}}.<ref name=Shisui/>

In November 1986, during the construction of the {{ill|Shisui Comprehensive Park|ja|酒々井総合公園}}, a one-month excavation was conducted. The mound features a 2-meter-wide surrounding moat and a protruding section. The main burial chamber, located at the center of the southern side of the mound, was identified as a {{ill|horizontal stone burial chamber|ja|横口式石槨|1=Side-entrance Sarcophagus Chamber}}. Based on the {{ill|sue ware|ja|須恵器|1=Sue pottery}} found on the terrace section, the kofun is believed to have been constructed in the late 7th to early 8th century. Restoration work was carried out in February 1987.

== References ==
{{Reflist}}

== Bibliography ==
* Shisui Town and Inba District designation1 Center. _Excavation Report on the Shisui Town Comprehensive Park Site: Onoue Hirohata Ruins and Sumikomorida Kofun._ 1987.
== See Also ==
* {{ill|List of kofun in Japan|ja|Infobox ancient site一覧}}

{{japanese-history-stub}}





























