'''Sumikomorida Kofun''' (墨小盛田古墳, also pronounced as Sumiko Morita Kofun<ref name=Shisui>{{Cite web|和書|author=Shisui Town Hall|url=https://www.town.shisui.chiba.jp/navi/mobile/id/374.html|title=Sumikomorida Kofun|work=Shisui Tourism Navi|accessdate=2020-08-20}}</ref>) is a {{ill|Square Kofun|ja|方墳|1=Square Kofun|1=Square Kofun|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Square Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Square Kofun|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} located in [[:en:Shisui|Shisui, Chiba]], [[:en:Chiba Prefecture|Chiba Prefecture]], Japan.

== Overview ==
The Kofun measures approximately 30 meters north-south, 23 meters east-west, and 3 meters in height. {{ill|Rectangular Kofun|lt=Rectangular Kofuns|ja|長方形墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rectangular Kofun|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} are a characteristic type of kofun found in the [[:en:Shimōsa Province|Shimousa Province]] region during the late [[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]].<ref name=Shisui/>

In November 1986, during the construction of the {{ill|Shisui Comprehensive Park|ja|酒々井総合公園|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shisui Comprehensive Park|qq=}}, a one-month excavation was conducted. The mound features a 2-meter-wide surrounding moat and a protruding section. The main burial chamber, located at the center of the southern side of the mound, was identified as a {{ill|horizontal stone burial chamber|ja|横口式石槨|1=Side-entrance Sarcophagus Chamber|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/horizontal stone burial chamber|13=User:Immanuelle/Side-entrance Sarcophagus Chamber|qq=}}. Based on the [[:en:Sue pottery|Sue pottery]] found on the terrace section, the kofun is believed to have been constructed in the late 7th to early 8th century. Restoration work was carried out in February 1987.

